{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a85f7605-9a34-4904-8d3c-6e30d207713b","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py` line 3** — `datetime.now()`\n\n```python\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\n**Why it's untestable:** Calling `datetime.now()` directly makes it impossible to freeze or mock time in tests. The output changes on every run.\n\n**Recommended fix:** Inject the clock dependency via `django.utils.timezone.now` and use [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) or `unittest.mock.patch` in tests:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis is a small project — only **1 instance** found. Using `timezone.now()` also gives you timezone-aware datetimes, which Django expects when `USE_TZ = True`. Want me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"22ac55ed-a2b9-4736-9a7e-a41052eabc32","outputTokens":228,"requestId":"E3C4:3454B1:27AB769:2B8D073:6A053CE3"},"id":"eb216f60-d4ca-4672-a98b-dfc667368d73","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:09:29.930Z","parentId":"63a7dd75-d59c-4598-9fcb-51c6a9ed1a4d"}
